        "text": "No. There is no legal requirement to remove asbestos before selling a Brisbane home. Bonded asbestos that is intact and in good condition is generally best left undisturbed. Sellers have three realistic options: leave it undisturbed and disclose, remediate before listing, or disclose the condition and price accordingly. The right approach depends on the type of asbestos, its condition, and the likely buyer pool for your property."
      }
