      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Queensland has no specific statutory requirement to disclose asbestos in a residential property sale, unlike some other states. However, sellers and agents have a general obligation not to mislead buyers and must disclose known material facts. If you are aware asbestos is present and do not disclose it, that could constitute a misleading omission. The practical standard is: if you know it is there, disclose it. Having an asbestos register prepared by a licensed assessor before listing is best practice and protects you from claims later."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does asbestos affect the buyer pool when selling in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
